missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:28:- The Tao comparator is underspecified. What exact feature is the averaged model supposed to destroy: phase-sensitive triad geometry, sign-polarized transport, or a nontrivial coupling between scales and chirality? If that feature is not formalized before the comparison, "Tao-sensitive" will be backfilled from whatever survives the chosen decomposition.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:31:- The step also assumes that the full equation's coupled invariant geometry is richer than what the averaged model preserves. That may be true in spirit, but it is not enough. Many exact phase-sensitive distinctions are mathematically real and still too weak to change any blowup-facing estimate.
